Topic: TAT (Thematic Apperception Test) 🧠🔥

👉 This is part of Psychology Tests (Day 2 in SSB)
👉 Here, your subconscious mind is tested

1️⃣ What is TAT?

You will be shown 12 pictures + 1 blank slide

For each picture:

⏱️ 30 sec → Observe

⏱️ 4 min → Write story

👉 Total: 13 stories

🖼️ Example of TAT Picture

👉 Pictures may show:

Problems

Daily life situations

Emotional scenes

2️⃣ What SSB Checks in TAT

They check your:

Thinking style

Attitude

Problem-solving ability

Leadership

Responsibility

👉 Your story = Your personality

3️⃣ Story Structure (Follow THIS Always)
🔹 1. Character (Hero = YOU)

Age, role

Positive mindset

🔹 2. Situation (Present)

What is happening

🔹 3. Action (MOST IMPORTANT)

Steps taken to solve problem

🔹 4. Result (Positive Ending)

Problem solved

Lesson learned

🧠 GOLDEN RULES

✅ Keep story simple & realistic
✅ Show action, not thinking only
✅ Be positive
✅ Show leadership + responsibility

4️⃣ Special Case – Blank Slide

👉 Last slide = No image

You can write:

Your life goal

Real-life experience

Future plan

💥 Best approach:
👉 Write your aim to become an officer with actions

5️⃣ Example Story

“A 21-year-old engineering student Akshay noticed that many students in his college struggled with placements. He organized weekly group discussions and aptitude sessions. With consistent effort, many students improved and secured jobs. His initiative boosted confidence among peers.”

6️⃣ Common Mistakes

❌ Negative endings (death, failure)
❌ Imaginary/filmy stories
❌ No action taken
❌ Too emotional / unrealistic
❌ Different personality in each story

7️⃣ PRO STRATEGY (VERY IMPORTANT)

👉 Show these qualities in stories:

Initiative

Leadership

Responsibility

Helping nature

Practical thinking

👉 Keep same personality in all stories
💥 Consistency = Selection

8️⃣ Practice Task

Take any random situation and write:

1️⃣ Who is the main character?
2️⃣ What is the problem?
3️⃣ What actions will you take?
4️⃣ What is the final result?

⏱️ Time: 4 minutes

